# AstroConnect Design System for Android (Kotlin)

This guide provides the color palette, gradients, typography, and component styles from the AstroConnect web application for implementation in your Kotlin Android app.

## 1. Color Palette

Define these in your `res/values/colors.xml`.

### Primary Colors (Space & Purple)
| Name | Hex Code | Android Usage Suggestion |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `space_900` | `#0f172a` | Primary Background, Status Bar |
| `space_800` | `#1e293b` | Cards, Bottom Sheets, Dark Surfaces |
| `space_700` | `#334155` | Borders, Dividers, Muted Text |
| `purple_600` | `#6366f1` | Primary Actions, FABs, Links |
| `purple_500` | `#8b5cf6` | Accents, Secondary Buttons |
| `purple_100` | `#e0e7ff` | Light Backgrounds (Chips, Bubbles) |

### Accent Colors (Gold & Orange)
| Name | Hex Code | Android Usage Suggestion |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `gold_500` | `#f59e0b` | Icons, Rating Stars, Warnings |
| `gold_400` | `#fbbf24` | Gradient Start for Gold |
| `orange_600` | `#ea580c` | Brand Text, Specific Actions |
